subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Plate 7
). Uncus with central excavation, socius long curved and slender; tegumen with two lateral appendages; valva ovate, saccus over half of the length of valva, slightly swollen in middle. Aedeagus longer than distance from saccus to socius, narrow, with a weakly defined cornutus, and a few small spines appended to terminal quarter. Pleural lobes with one edge sclerotised.

Female genitalia (
Plate 17
). Lamella postvaginalis evenly curved, ostium conical, ductus bursae long and scobinate for its whole length, corpus bursae ovoid, signum almost cruciform with spines arranged laterally.
